<sec id="id-2b000d57-2c46-485e-b95a-06f9a3726576"><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7bdb1541-ec5a-4c00-b6c5-eaf2b5721731" timestamp="1627519673218"?>Informed consent and learning transaction<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7bdb1541-ec5a-4c00-b6c5-eaf2b5721731"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="6861742" change-id="2cc34320-7b17-404c-a81c-ba257d3f61fa" text="See Annex below “Open-edi Reference Model and Learning transaction” provides informative information on the key modelling constructs introduced in ISO/IEC 29187-1." timestamp="1633268121770"?></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="46f44bc5-4340-4a8d-9f01-643e93a1370c" timestamp="1627568714736"?>A key privacy protection requirement is that it requires <underline>informed consent</underline><xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-05b5e652-638d-44b1-b1c1-e312a6e7da83.xml#id-e1d8788b-c59e-4688-e3c8-9638cbb25fef" id="id-21ce90e3-7812-4c68-b3ff-5f230c92bc0a" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-e1d8788b-c59e-4688-e3c8-9638cbb25fef"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="46f44bc5-4340-4a8d-9f01-643e93a1370c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="e09fb54a-e064-4a75-aff5-72eceacf90f1" timestamp="1633268147647"?>See <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e09fb54a-e064-4a75-aff5-72eceacf90f1"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4d36bc04-fbc5-4e3a-c828-7d83a44eead3" timestamp="1627568714736"?><xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-37fc310f-b2a7-4d37-928b-cfb02ad87813.xml#id-1106b628-60e0-495a-9bf4-8afc93512899" ref-type="app" id="id-8647eb44-f0e1-4e21-a762-59c96be35afc" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4d36bc04-fbc5-4e3a-c828-7d83a44eead3"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="644b902c-9c44-41be-9d1d-c669428a179e" timestamp="1633268147647"?> below “Open-edi Reference Model and Learning transaction” provides informative information on the key modelling constructs introduced in ISO/IEC 29187-1.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="644b902c-9c44-41be-9d1d-c669428a179e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="bc0d314d-3c72-492f-c650-0586e864461c" timestamp="1627568714736"?></p></fn> of the individual, including in the role of an individual learner. It also requires the identification of the purpose(s), goal for which the personal information is to be created/collected, used, managed, shared, deleted, etc. In addition to identifying purpose(s) and informed consent (presented below) as Privacy Protection principles in Clauses <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-6a6c5f54-264f-41d4-bc3d-a3ac6a712589.xml#id-7004a606-408d-4581-c4b7-7c00eddde914" ref-type="sec" id="id-9806e8cc-21cd-4b8a-d806-99ef23e2c51d" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref> and <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-1323f2dc-f399-45cb-b8c0-0ef5f5e7b109.xml#id-07fb8710-17d0-4e1a-f3c5-dac04cac8fbb" ref-type="sec" id="id-b28cc18a-a6e0-4dd2-b621-57f7449ee318" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>. There are also the Privacy Protection Principles of “accountability” of “limiting collection”, “limiting use, disclosure and retention”, “accuracy”, “openness”, “individual access”, and “challenging compliance” (presented below Privacy Protection principles in Clauses <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-6a6c5f54-264f-41d4-bc3d-a3ac6a712589.xml#id-7004a606-408d-4581-c4b7-7c00eddde914" ref-type="sec" id="id-049249e7-dc2e-43f1-c237-773338644f7e" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>, <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-b98a091d-4661-4b58-9d55-913bff9a56f1.xml#id-bfd4e2af-db23-4738-819b-7e10ea494e6b" ref-type="sec" id="id-fe817ffd-d62c-4bc1-cfc9-d3aa8b24751a" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>, 5.3.5, 5.3.6, 5.3.7, 5.3.9, 5.3.10, and 5.3.11 respectively).<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="bc0d314d-3c72-492f-c650-0586e864461c"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6709b608-641c-415e-b228-53228710032c" timestamp="1627792385555"?>Requirements of this nature focus on what might be considered the LET operational view (LOV). In addition, there are ICT technical support requirements for privacy protection principles .xml#8 “safeguards” (see <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6709b608-641c-415e-b228-53228710032c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="047e1b24-7e20-4c2d-a62d-cfb213cece6f" timestamp="1633090351167"?>Clause <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="047e1b24-7e20-4c2d-a62d-cfb213cece6f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="480fd9b8-dcb9-4733-ce70-7c1fcb16dbbd" timestamp="1627792385555"?><xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-8e006e2b-645b-4725-a647-e0b01168cd36.xml#id-9c3d0f2e-ebe9-42fb-824e-45c46d10a0b7" ref-type="sec" id="id-2c47a22b-7269-4fec-86b5-4da9fc5c1c9e" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="480fd9b8-dcb9-4733-ce70-7c1fcb16dbbd"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="93b9618d-b1c9-4ae7-eb8c-7f8aaa00ff8b" timestamp="1633268378657"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="93b9618d-b1c9-4ae7-eb8c-7f8aaa00ff8b"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f4901965-eda5-488a-f730-d5495d25de62" timestamp="1627792385555"?>below). These include security services, communication services, etc.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f4901965-eda5-488a-f730-d5495d25de62"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="87e93e1f-150c-4f98-e0c7-5b2e7dc9d1c3" timestamp="1627519735989"?>Requirements of this nature are not unique to a LET (or ITLET) context. They have already been identified and addressed in a generic manner in the ISO/IEC 14662 <italic>Open-edi Reference Model</italic> as being a “transaction” nature in support of an agreed upon commitment exchange between an individual learner and a LET provider.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="87e93e1f-150c-4f98-e0c7-5b2e7dc9d1c3"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="db59b763-526c-4d1c-cfa8-6f785cf0c157" timestamp="1631272650946"?>Consequently, the “LET Privacy Protection Framework and Reference Model” (presented below in <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-05b5e652-638d-44b1-b1c1-e312a6e7da83.xml#id-029ad151-b689-4ea7-ad85-d366785209c1" ref-type="fig" id="id-70154ab2-dfbb-485a-d76b-c5d3e8c1a878" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>) is based on the ISO/IEC 14662 standard <italic>Open-edi Reference Model</italic>. A key construct of the Open-edi Reference Model is that it recognizes that a commitment exchange, modelled as a transaction, needs to be treated and supported as a whole. At the same time, and from an ICT (including ITLET perspective) it is recognized that ICT-based support services, i.e., functional support services view change as ICT changes on the whole, but those of the user and operational requirements view remain fairly constant. The interaction and inter-working between (a) the user operational view; and, (b) the ICT support services view in modelling a transaction, and then developing standards in support of the same as presented in the Open-edi Reference Model as the need to differentiate between the business operation view (BOV) and functional services view (FSV).<xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-05b5e652-638d-44b1-b1c1-e312a6e7da83.xml#id-8175d7e6-19a5-4d70-97e5-e95d56e18743" id="id-18c4fc9e-85c9-448b-9b97-efa3400b6132" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-8175d7e6-19a5-4d70-97e5-e95d56e18743"><p>See further below, <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="db59b763-526c-4d1c-cfa8-6f785cf0c157"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="6861742" change-id="e5bae6cc-7c36-4732-ead2-cfc03a8c0369" text="Annex " timestamp="1633268457539"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="d8e285f3-8609-44f7-daf5-adac2e194d80" timestamp="1631272650946"?><xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-37fc310f-b2a7-4d37-928b-cfb02ad87813.xml#id-1106b628-60e0-495a-9bf4-8afc93512899" ref-type="app" id="id-33defb92-dd33-44e3-8a18-c2a09723eb77" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref> (informative) titled “<italic>Use and adaptation of the Open-edi Reference Model”.</italic></p></fn> LET privacy protection Framework and Reference Model uses these two views of the Open-edi Reference Model to describe the relevant aspects of a learning transaction:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d8e285f3-8609-44f7-daf5-adac2e194d80"?></p><list list-type="alpha-lower"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7e5d37ef-0b04-4d2b-f8dd-fdcb56f1bc7b" timestamp="1627519735989"?><list-item id="id-39202766-0c30-4f92-cb48-c784c91885e0"><p>the “Learning Operational View (LOV) aspects of a learning transaction; and,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-a52f3af7-3db5-40b6-d06e-620ec3610367"><p>the “LET- FSV view of a learning transaction.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7e5d37ef-0b04-4d2b-f8dd-fdcb56f1bc7b"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6d3b1305-22dd-4ae5-cf6e-7aa3f41bc238" timestamp="1627519735989"?>The Learning Operational View (LOV) addresses the aspects of the context and semantic aspects of personal information in a learning transaction including data management and interchange aspects. The LOV also can be referred to as the operational and user requirements view.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6d3b1305-22dd-4ae5-cf6e-7aa3f41bc238"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="bb828f8c-42c1-4abb-97c7-b716ea0eea35" timestamp="1627519735989"?>The LET-FSV addresses the ICT infrastructure and support services meeting the mechanical needs of the Learning Operational View. Its purpose is to support the demands on the supporting ICT infrastructure of the Learning Operational View. It focuses on ICT aspects of:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="bb828f8c-42c1-4abb-97c7-b716ea0eea35"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="458cfe92-f10e-4aaa-8f62-b007468895f5" timestamp="1627519741087"?><list-item id="id-71dc7ea8-f50a-409b-b6ff-80036a7c3dd0"><p>functional capabilities;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-72e21509-ccd7-4a91-cfcd-a8cdd39f9e6e"><p>service interfaces; and,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-5ba9cf3a-e957-4543-c05a-249522e39418"><p>protocols and APIs.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="458cfe92-f10e-4aaa-8f62-b007468895f5"?></list><fig id="id-029ad151-b689-4ea7-ad85-d366785209c1" specific-use="size:M"><caption><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="2963fc57-f814-43ff-edd0-74b5ca6bef59" timestamp="1627788217844"?>Learning Transaction - Privacy Protection – Framework and Reference Model<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2963fc57-f814-43ff-edd0-74b5ca6bef59"?></title></caption><graphic xlink:href="images/82851/1" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/></fig><p/></sec>
